  "The annual increase rate of property values": "",
  "A mill is one-tenth of a cent, or $1 per $1,000 of assessed value. A mill rate of 20 means $20 in tax per $1,000 of assessed value, equivalent to a 2% tax rate.": "",
  "What is a 'homestead exemption'?": "",
